A large proportion of the household respondents (94.4%; 
 n=302) perceived that they had experienced drought as the most frequent extreme event followed by extreme heat (74.7%; 
 n=239) (
 Figure 3). Key informants and FGD participants also confirmed that there have been changes in rainfall amount and temperature. One key informant stated
 

“2015/16 summer season has been the worst in terms of excessive heat. There were 2 days on a weekend that were the hottest ones we have ever seen. On those same days, our soya bean crops actually dried up within hours from the excessive heat. I think that temperatures at that time were over 40°C. On the other hand, we also experienced extremely cold periods in winter.”
